.TH "t3_phy_reset" 9 "t3_phy_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t3_phy_reset \- reset a PHY block
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t3_phy_reset
.BI "(struct cphy *phy "  ","
.BI "int mmd "  ","
.BI "int wait "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phy" 12
the PHY to operate on
.IP "mmd" 12
the device address of the PHY block to reset
.IP "wait" 12
how long to wait for the reset to complete in 1ms increments

Resets a PHY block and optionally waits for the reset to complete.
\fImmd\fP should be 0 for 10/100/1000 PHYs and the device address to reset
for 10G PHYs.
